indirect input activation of such neurons with non-ﬁxed latencies (Fig. 7 and Table 1). Of these IC neurons, 10 were inﬂuenced by RSS alone, 12 by LSS alone and 17 others were affected by both of these central neuro-

nal inputs. The predominant effect of stellate stimulation on IC activity was excitation (Table 1). Likewise, when low frequency electrical stimuli (1 Hz) were applied to either cervical vagus, the IC activity from 41% (38/92) of

